PHASE 2 — VISUALIZER (biggest LinkedIn impact)
──────────────────────────────────────────────

The visualizer has 3 layers. The C++ core is NOT changed — only a JSON
log output is added alongside existing pcap/text logs.

2a. C++ JSON event log (minimal change to existing Logger):
    Add a second output: sim_events.jsonl
    Each line format:
    {
      "ts": 1234567890,
      "from": "MME",
      "to": "HSS",
      "msg": "Diameter AIR",
      "interface": "S6a",
      "port": 3868,
      "hex": "00010203...",
      "sim": "4g",
      "beginner_text": "MME is asking HSS to verify the subscriber identity",
      "interview_q": "What does Command Code 318 mean in Diameter?",
      "interview_a": "CC 318 is Authentication-Information per TS 29.272..."
    }
    The beginner_text and interview_q/a come from a lookup in tag_rules.json
    at log time — NOT hardcoded per message. Use the tag matching system.

2b. Python WebSocket bridge: tools/viz_server.py
    - Tails sim_events.jsonl in real time using inotify / polling
    - Loads interview_questions/ folder using glob (all *.yaml files)
    - Loads tag_rules.json for pattern matching
    - On each new event: extracts tags via tag_rules.json pattern match,
      queries question bank for top 3 matching questions by tag overlap,
      appends matched questions to the event JSON
    - Serves WebSocket on ws://localhost:8765
    - Serves static viz_ui.html on http://localhost:8080
    - Requirements: only stdlib + `pip install websockets pyyaml`
    - One command to run: python3 tools/viz_server.py

2c. Browser UI: tools/viz_ui.html
    - Single self-contained HTML file, pure vanilla JS, NO npm, NO framework
    - Opens in any browser, connects to ws://localhost:8765 automatically
    - Three tabs: BEGINNER | ENGINEER | INTERVIEW
    - Center: live ladder diagram drawing itself as events arrive
      Nodes as vertical lifelines (auto-detected from sim field in event):
        4g:  UE — eNB — MME — HSS — SGW — PGW — PCRF
        ims: UE — P-CSCF — S-CSCF — MTAS — IMS-HSS
        5g:  gNB — AMF — UDM — AUSF — NRF — SMF
      Each message = animated arrow between two lifelines (300ms delay)
      Arrow label = message name
    - BEGINNER tab: plain English caption below each arrow, pastel colors,
      no hex, simple language
    - ENGINEER tab: arrow shows msg name + interface + port,
      click arrow = slide-in panel with hex bytes + field breakdown
